==English==
===Etymology===
From the Middle English and French ''[[confesser]],'' from the Old French ''[[confes]],'' from the Latin ''[[confessus]].''

===Verb===
'''to confess'''

# To admit to the truth, particularly in the context of sins or crimes committed
# To disclose or reveal

